<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-20T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-20T16:00:00-05:00" n="380" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7409a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Neville</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-20T16:00:00-05:00">November 20, 1935—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>178. Press despatches from Tokyo state that Foreign Office has issued
                            denial that “the Japanese Government was in any way responsible for the
                            autonomy movement” in North China.</p>
                        <p>Please cable text of such statement if issued and texts of other official
                            Japanese statements relative to North China situation if and when
                            made.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>